parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause a fire, leading to damage to the vehicle and potentially putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from under the hood
burning smell
dashboard lights flickering or going out
engine stalling or not starting
electrical system malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience and potentially putting the driver and passengers at risk of being stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling or not starting
difficulty starting the engine
dashboard lights flickering or going out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including stalling, not starting, and electrical fires, which can put the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Dashboard lights flickering or going out
engine stalling or not starting
electrical system malfunctioning
burning smell
smoke or flames coming from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to upshift can cause the engine to rev excessively, leading to loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential engine damage.
symptoms: The transmission fails to upshift above 3rd or 4th gear
the engine RPM increases excessively
the vehicle accelerates slowly
and the transmission makes unusual noises.

symptoms: The transmission slips or pops out of gear
the engine RPM increases excessively
the vehicle loses power
and the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission leak and seal failure can cause the transmission to fail, leading to costly repairs and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission leaks fluid
the seal is broken
and the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to accelerate, and potentially leading to accidents.

the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The power window failure can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues.
symptoms: The front passenger side power window plastic assembly breaks
causing the window to malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Axle and CV Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear axle and CV joint failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential damage to other vehicle components.
symptoms: The rear axle spline falls out
and the boots to CV joints fall off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling or Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected stalling or loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic, and can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning

vibrates badly when idling
and may require pumping the gas pedal to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause serious damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure, and can also pose a risk of engine fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause poor engine performance, stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle has poor gas mileage
and the engine module may need to be replaced.

symptoms: The seat belt does not retract properly

the seat belt does not restrain the passenger
the seat belt unfastens while wearing

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized shoulder/lap belt can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The driver/passenger front shoulder/lap belt won't retract into the door assembly
the belt unfastens while wearing
and the belt does not restrain the driver/passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seat belt locking issues can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.

and the seat belt does not restrain the passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to skids, loss of control, and increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents or near-misses.

the brakes perform erratically.

symptoms: The brakes make a noise

the brakes vibrate when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause the brakes to vibrate, make noise, or fail to stop the vehicle properly, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to perform erratically, leading to loss of control and increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
